DESIGNATIONS: UNITED WAY OF NORTHWEST FLORIDA REQUIRES AN AGENCY TO BE CLASSIFIED AS A 501(C)(3) EXEMPT ORGANIZATION TO RECEIVE DESIGNATED FUNDS FROM DONORS. UNITED WAY OF NORTHWEST FLORIDA REQUIRES EACH DESIGNATED AGENCY TO RETURN A FORM THAT PROVES THEIR 501 (C) (3) STATUS. RETURN OF ANTI-TERRORISM COMPLIANCE MEASURES FORM BEFORE RELEASE OF FUNDS.

THE CHIEF VOLUNTEER OF EACH UNITED WAY AFFILIATED AGENCY WILL AUTOMATICALLY BE A MEMBER AND SHALL BE ENTITLED TO ATTEND AND VOTE AT ALL MEMBERSHIP MEETINGS DURING THE TIME THEY HOLD SUCH POSITION. EACH CONTRIBUTOR TO THE UNITED WAY SHALL BE A MEMBER OF THIS CORPORATION FOR THE YEAR FOR WHICH THAT CONTRIBUTOR'S CONTRIBUTION WAS GIVEN AND AS A MEMBER SHALL BE ENTITLED TO ATTEND AND VOTE AT ALL MEMBERSHIP MEETINGS DURING THAT PERIOD.
THE MEMBERS APPROVE THE SELECTION OF THE INCOMING BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

THE TAX RETURN WAS REVIEWED BY THE PRESIDENT/CEO AND VP/COO, AS WELL AS SUBMITTED ELECTRONICALLY TO ALL BOARD MEMBERS.
GOVERNING BOARD MEMBERS ARE REQUIRED TO REVIEW THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY WITHIN THE CODE OF ETHICS, AND SIGN A STATEMENT CONFIRMING THEIR COMPLIANCE OR DISCLOSING POTENTIAL CONFLICTS ANNUALLY.
UNITED WAY'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND FORM 990 ARE AVAILABLE ON THE ORGANIZATION'S WEBSITE. THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.
